Lux: You’re better than me. Better than all of us... I see that now.
Player: Why…? You didn’t have to—
Lux: All this time... I thought she robbed me...
Player: Karol took your pain. Your death.
Lux: I know now... Mother saw what I didn’t...
Lux: ...That love isn’t measured in power, but in what you shield others from.
Lux: Don’t make my mistake. Protect them... *differently*.\
The Sorcerech is not just about power…
Player: If I can’t make you hear each other…\
Then let me help you remember.
